                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">First and foremost - Make it so you don't have to tash to get a reliable charm. That's HUGE, when you get right down to it.
<br />

<br />
Right now you have a 3 pull ... no way in hell am I going to charm, because it's probably going to last under 20 seconds and cause more harm then good.
<br />

<br />
That's the problem with charm - it really is only useful as a solo tool or in a group designed around charm.
<br />

<br />
I would love to have the scenario back, where you have a 3 pull, charm one and send it against the other (as in ... CROWD CONTROL), your group fights the first, and by god your charm will probably last more then a few seconds without tash. THAT would make me love the charm nerf, if the resists on mobs were lowered.
<br />

<br />
I have TD3 ... let me feel relatively comfortable in having charm up in my lineup as a <span style="font-weight: bold">method of crowd control.</span>
<br />

<br />
Give me this chance and I'll be a very happy camper, even with my pet dps cut in half.[/b]</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />It's easy to use - if you're one of the 2% of the population who thinks logically and can read an instruction manual. The other 98% of the population would find it very hard or impossible to use.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
