                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The charm nerf isn't acceptable.
<br />

<br />
It's a way for SoE to dig themselves out of the hole they've dug with the Time candyland - creating a minority of players with two, three, and nearly four times the HP, Mana, and other stats beyond that of those that have yet to make it to that place.
<br />

<br />
OoW is GoD 2.0 - I haven't seen it, haven't tested it, but I feel it in my bones to be true.  This nerf won't be the last example of "tuning".  The news is already leaking out about other things - shared spell line recasts for one.  SoE is backpeddling tremendously.  All in an effort to keep the content from being rolled over in the first 30 days by those with the best gear in the game.
<br />

<br />
They already know that most of the OoW content is not doable by 90 pct of the community.  They won't own up to it - but the facts are there if you read through some of the BS.
<br />

<br />
Here's what I guess you'll see in a few hours as a 65:
<br />

<br />
1-2 zones of light blue- low dark blue "trash" that yields very poor experience, a couple drops like you've seen in Natimbi and Qinimi
<br />

<br />
Then 3 zones that are doable by pre-Ele 65 - IF they have 2 healers in group and people are on the ball.  Ferubi, Barindu, Hard Ldon, sewers - topping out at Tipt/Vxed hitting mobs.
<br />

<br />
Beyond that it's gonna be like trying to single group Vindi.
<br />

<br />
What pisses me off to no end is that with full dps charm - I could have a chance in those zones (not solo, or even duo really).  And so could a lot of others.  The only incentives to this expansion are "woot I'm level 70" - despite the fact that you will never see half your spells (if you're in the 90 pct).  Toss in a few AA (nothing in the chanter line looks like anything to write home about to me) for specific classes (druid/shaman call to corpse in particular).  Extra spell cell (probably the #1 request of all chanters since Kunark) for 3 AA.  They're going to sell some copies.
<br />

<br />
They won't sell one to me tomorrow.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><span style="color: darkblue"> 
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=831098" target="_blank" class="postlink">Visionary Nokei Orhaste</a></span>
<br />
Coercer for <span style="color: blue"><a href="http://www.houseofaegis.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">House of Aegis</a></span>
<br />
Luclin
<br />
&lt;Retiring 11/02/04&gt;
<br />

<br />
E66.191/L h++ 2.8khp 4.6km ft12 BK10
<br />

<br />
It`s never fun until the druid dies.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
