                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok, it's obvious that they consider charm DPS to be too much.
<br />

<br />
Remove all previous penalties on charm spells, including:
<br />

<br />
1) the charm exp penalty
<br />
2) the resist mod on CoD (and add one to the OoW charms)
<br />
3) the focus effects nerf
<br />

<br />
In addition:
<br />

<br />
4) Make a LOT of mobs charmable. I mean a LOT. I should have to wrack my brain, thinking through the vast list of mobs that are charmable, if I'm trying to remember whether that mob that's inc is charmable or not. Alternatively, instead of memorizing the 3 models of mobs that are charmable, I should have to memorize the 3 models of mobs that AREN'T charmable.
<br />

<br />

<br />
I think instituting these 4 changes would do a significant amount to level the playing field for charm. I feel that a well balanced spell usable in many areas is better than a poorly balanced spell usable in only a few. I also feel, however, that the reward for charming has been vastly reduced, and that in order for charm to still be useful, you have to reduce the risk some - I don't really like the idea of making the DPS reduction last longer than the charm duration by a few seconds, though. I'd rather see a resist mod on our charms reimplemented.
<br />

<br />
It would be GREAT to see charm pets on more raid encounters as well, to make up for the fact that this expansion, like all the rest, will no doubt have fights where we do nothing but nuke.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
