                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It is too bad that SOE just doesnt make the mobs more intelligent.  I think what SOE wants to limit are: how much experience a group or soloer can make in a period of time and to limit the charmed mob from trivializing a boss encounter.
<br />

<br />
Why not leave charm the way it is and do these 2 things.  This may even save the Bards.
<br />

<br />
1.) Cap the experience a person or group can make in a hour...after you make so much....you dont get anymore experience for your kills....I mean that is really what you guys really want.  This will stop almost all exploits.
<br />

<br />
2. ) Adjust the AI of the boss mob, so that he/she casts dispell magic on charmed pets first....I would do this if I saw a charm pet coming after me.  Heck, if you are worried about a bunch of enchanters ganging up on the boss, let the dispell be AE.  After the dispell, you got a bunch more enemies (in the ex pets).
<br />

<br />
If charm in its present form is removed from the game, what is SOE vision for the enchanter class?  Are we to just buff and log?  Even though it is widely know that enchanters can add tremendous dps to a group, I dont see groups asking me to join them because of this....in fact most groups unless they understand charm prefer to NOT have this risk in their groups.  The groups that allow me to charm are basically my friends, pickup groups get very nervous when I charm.
<br />

<br />
