                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">LOL, suddenly that top 10'ner where 'Mobs act confused when charm breaks' is looking gorgeous right about now.
<br />

<br />
  1. Remove the XP penalty where any mitigated damage is dealt via an OoW charm ( or previous since it could be retrofitted ).
<br />

<br />
  2. Dumb down the risk somewhat, since the risk is skewed -- via stuns, confusion, maybe some component of TD3 or for a kick in the groin an AA that requires TD3 to kick in,  whatever the hell you want to do.   Scale the risk.
<br />

<br />
  3.  'Refix'  ( this was a bug wasn't it that was fixed?  Correct me if I'm wrong here  )  the 'rule of 4' BS so that we can have non-leeching useful group members with our dumbed-down pets.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Kith of VS</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
