                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">It's really simple.
<br />

<br />
Charm FUBARS the devs plans for encounters. (I'll not comment on "plans" being a HORRIBLE way to design an encounter.)
<br />

<br />
QUIT ... DANCING ... AROUND ... THE ... ISSUE
<br />

<br />
Remove charm.
<br />
Make all non-giant/dragon-class mobs stunable.
<br />
Triple the HP on Shiny Bob.
<br />
Done.
<br />

<br />
No one can charm, so the Ultra-DPS problem goes away. Enchanters should NEVER have been a DPS class. We are, in my opinion, the air traffic controllers of combat. Let us return to that.
<br />

<br />
Bright Frigging Lord God Agnostic are they that freaking clueless??
<br />

<br />
Premise: Charm breaks the game.
<br />
Solution: Don't allow charm.
<br />

<br />
They've done it before....
<br />

<br />
Premise: Call of the Hero breaks "insert zone here"
<br />
Solution: Call of the Hero doesn't work in "insert zone here"</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
